{LOCAL FARMING.                        
      All but the poorest land is      
 farmed intensively.  Even the steepest
 slopes are considered suitable for    
 ploughing and major crops include     
 cereal, potato and kale. The winter   
 climate in this area is mild enough to
 grow crops such as Winter Barley.     
 There are also large herds of sheep   
 and dairy cattle, such as Devon Red.  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
